1
00:00:50,600 --> 00:00:51,479
What are you doing here?

2
00:00:53,119 --> 00:00:53,960
Siqi...

3
00:00:55,640 --> 00:00:56,320
Your dad...

4
00:00:58,079 --> 00:00:58,679
He's gone.

5
00:01:12,719 --> 00:01:14,159
My condolences to the family.

6
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:21,879
Husband...

7
00:01:23,159 --> 00:01:24,040
You just left like that...

8
00:01:24,040 --> 00:01:26,640
What are we supposed to do now, all alone?

9
00:01:26,640 --> 00:01:27,640
Husband...

10
00:01:28,239 --> 00:01:29,159
How fake.

11
00:01:30,200 --> 00:01:31,840
You killed my dad.

12
00:01:32,680 --> 00:01:33,920
Don't accuse me falsely.

13
00:01:33,920 --> 00:01:34,840
Are you out of your mind?

14
00:01:36,480 --> 00:01:37,840
He was fine when I left.

15
00:01:38,040 --> 00:01:39,120
But when I came back...

16
00:01:39,120 --> 00:01:40,439
the oxygen mask had come off.

17
00:01:40,799 --> 00:01:41,840
You were scared.

18
00:01:42,280 --> 00:01:43,480
You were scared my dad would wake up,

19
00:01:43,879 --> 00:01:45,560
and find out about you and Jiang Min.

20
00:01:45,879 --> 00:01:47,280
Then you'd have nothing left.

21
00:01:47,280 --> 00:01:49,120
So you killed him.

22
00:01:49,439 --> 00:01:50,959
The doctors said it was an accident.

23
00:01:51,200 --> 00:01:52,519
Stop talking nonsense here!

24
00:01:52,760 --> 00:01:54,480
Keep it up, and I won't hold back!

25
00:01:54,480 --> 00:01:56,319
What, you wanna kill me too now?

26
00:01:56,519 --> 00:01:57,799
Show some respect.

27
00:01:59,640 --> 00:02:00,879
Touch her and see what happens.

28
00:02:04,959 --> 00:02:05,680
Lin Siqi.

29
00:02:06,239 --> 00:02:07,200
If you've got time to doubt me,

30
00:02:07,200 --> 00:02:08,199
why not doubt him?

31
00:02:08,919 --> 00:02:10,039
Think about it.

32
00:02:10,400 --> 00:02:12,000
The day your dad fell down the stairs,

33
00:02:12,240 --> 00:02:14,280
he went to his engagement announcement with Jiang Lai.

34
00:02:14,800 --> 00:02:16,039
And yesterday, the oxygen mask came off and he died.

35
00:02:16,039 --> 00:02:17,159
He was there too.

36
00:02:17,599 --> 00:02:18,759
Don't you think that's suspicious?

37
00:02:24,639 --> 00:02:26,759
Sneaking into the room at night with no lights on...

38
00:02:27,120 --> 00:02:28,719
If it wasn't you, who else could it be?

39
00:02:31,479 --> 00:02:32,159
Believe me.

40
00:02:32,680 --> 00:02:33,520
When I came in,

41
00:02:33,840 --> 00:02:34,840
your dad was already gone.

42
00:02:36,719 --> 00:02:37,719
Then tell me,

43
00:02:38,159 --> 00:02:39,520
what were you doing coming in at midnight?

44
00:02:39,520 --> 00:02:40,840
Who the hell are you?

45
00:02:41,240 --> 00:02:42,400
Why should I explain anything to you?

46
00:02:43,599 --> 00:02:45,319
Sounds like you're guilty.

47
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:48,560
Lin Siqi, you've really outdone yourself.

48
00:02:49,039 --> 00:02:50,120
First Zhang Xiaobei,

49
00:02:50,120 --> 00:02:51,159
then Sheng Yuanzhou,

50
00:02:51,159 --> 00:02:52,159
dragging your dad back and forth,

51
00:02:52,159 --> 00:02:53,319
until you wore your dad to death, huh?

52
00:02:55,919 --> 00:02:56,520
Liu Li.

53
00:02:57,360 --> 00:02:57,879
I'm telling you,

54
00:03:00,639 --> 00:03:03,199
I'll find out who the killer is.

55
00:03:04,199 --> 00:03:06,280
If I find out you had anything to do with this,

56
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:08,599
I won't let you off.

57
00:03:10,199 --> 00:03:12,000
With your dad in that position,

58
00:03:12,280 --> 00:03:14,120
no one around him meant well.

59
00:03:14,280 --> 00:03:15,800
Plenty of people wanted him dead.

60
00:03:16,439 --> 00:03:17,560
Whoever it was,

61
00:03:18,280 --> 00:03:20,120
I'll leave no stone unturned to find them.

62
00:03:20,120 --> 00:03:21,240
I'll make them pay.

63
00:03:22,039 --> 00:03:23,479
When the Sheng family wants to find someone,

64
00:03:23,960 --> 00:03:24,960
there's no one we can't find.

65
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:29,479
You don't call the shots in the Sheng family yet.

66
00:03:30,639 --> 00:03:32,280
Let's see what you can really do.

67
00:03:50,919 --> 00:03:52,759
Siqi, don't worry.

68
00:03:53,360 --> 00:03:55,360
I'll fight this battle with you, and we'll win.

69
00:03:56,120 --> 00:03:57,120
Right now, the first thing to do

70
00:03:57,560 --> 00:03:58,439
is to pull yourself together.

71
00:03:59,479 --> 00:04:01,080
Liu Li won't let this go.

72
00:04:01,879 --> 00:04:02,840
We need to be ready,

73
00:04:03,159 --> 00:04:04,199
in case she has any other tricks.

74
00:04:13,560 --> 00:04:14,639
You're in a hurry, aren't you?

75
00:04:15,039 --> 00:04:16,439
My dad's funeral hasn't even happened yet,

76
00:04:16,680 --> 00:04:18,120
and you're already rushing to read the will.

77
00:04:18,480 --> 00:04:20,160
Isn't this just securing what's yours?

78
00:04:20,720 --> 00:04:23,399
The sooner it's announced, the sooner we can relax.

79
00:04:24,399 --> 00:04:26,279
Heaven's still looking out for me.

80
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:29,240
All those years with your dad weren't for nothing.

81
00:04:29,759 --> 00:04:30,519
Don't worry.

82
00:04:30,839 --> 00:04:32,680
I'll expose who you really are.

83
00:04:33,680 --> 00:04:34,920
Now I will read the will.

84
00:04:38,519 --> 00:04:40,439
Two properties under Mr. Lin Chengren's name,

85
00:04:40,959 --> 00:04:41,680
and two cars,

86
00:04:42,160 --> 00:04:43,759
will all go to his wife, Liu Li.

87
00:04:44,519 --> 00:04:46,199
In addition, 2.31 million in savings

88
00:04:46,360 --> 00:04:48,360
and 7.44 million in fund investments

89
00:04:48,839 --> 00:04:49,959
will be inherited by his three children,

90
00:04:50,519 --> 00:04:52,519
Lin Siqi, Lin Siming, and Lin Sida,

91
00:04:52,519 --> 00:04:53,240
to be split equally.

92
00:04:53,639 --> 00:04:54,839
The 36 percent stake in Benevolent Medical

93
00:04:54,839 --> 00:04:57,000
held by Lin Chengren

94
00:04:57,000 --> 00:04:57,759
will be distributed as follows.

95
00:04:58,439 --> 00:05:00,319
Eldest daughter Lin Siqi: 18 percent.

96
00:05:00,519 --> 00:05:02,040
Second child Lin Siming: nine percent.

97
00:05:02,279 --> 00:05:03,720
Youngest child Lin Sida: nine percent.

98
00:05:04,120 --> 00:05:05,120
That concludes the will.

99
00:05:06,040 --> 00:05:07,920
No way. This will is fake, isn't it?

100
00:05:08,519 --> 00:05:09,319
This will

101
00:05:09,759 --> 00:05:11,279
was handled personally by Mr. Lin Chengren

102
00:05:11,560 --> 00:05:13,120
at our law firm while he was alive.

103
00:05:13,720 --> 00:05:14,639
We have witnesses,

104
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:15,800
as well as documents and recordings.

105
00:05:16,360 --> 00:05:18,600
I was there when Lin Chengren made the will.

106
00:05:18,600 --> 00:05:19,439
That 18 percent

107
00:05:19,439 --> 00:05:20,639
of Benevolent Medical was mine.

108
00:05:20,639 --> 00:05:22,000
Lin Siqi wasn't supposed to get any of it.

109
00:05:22,360 --> 00:05:22,879
That's true.

110
00:05:23,240 --> 00:05:24,920
In the previous will, you were the heir.

111
00:05:25,639 --> 00:05:27,959
Lin Siqi didn't inherit any shares.

112
00:05:28,920 --> 00:05:30,079
But last month,

113
00:05:30,480 --> 00:05:31,600
the day before Mr. Lin Chengren

114
00:05:32,040 --> 00:05:33,480
had his accident,

115
00:05:34,120 --> 00:05:36,360
he came to our firm and changed the will.

116
00:05:36,519 --> 00:05:37,759
You can check the date on it.

117
00:05:42,759 --> 00:05:44,959
Lin Chengren, how could you do this to me?

118
00:05:45,399 --> 00:05:46,399
The will has been read.

119
00:05:47,160 --> 00:05:47,839
I'll take my leave now.

120
00:05:48,000 --> 00:05:49,120
Wang Esq., I'll see you out.

121
00:05:56,360 --> 00:05:57,639
Don't be so shameless.

122
00:05:58,120 --> 00:05:59,480
Leaving a house to someone like you...

123
00:05:59,800 --> 00:06:01,639
you should thank Heaven for its mercy.

124
00:06:01,920 --> 00:06:02,279
No.

125
00:06:03,160 --> 00:06:04,319
You should thank my dad.

126
00:06:19,680 --> 00:06:21,959
Hey, pretty girl, you're real cute.

127
00:06:22,319 --> 00:06:23,879
How about you don't leave tonight?

128
00:06:26,680 --> 00:06:27,439
Behave yourself.

129
00:06:28,079 --> 00:06:29,439
Come with us, nice and easy.

130
00:06:31,079 --> 00:06:31,439
Don't move.

131
00:06:54,360 --> 00:06:55,199
Be good, yeah?

132
00:07:00,040 --> 00:07:00,519
Siqi!

133
00:07:03,160 --> 00:07:03,480
Come here.

134
00:07:07,240 --> 00:07:08,199
You got scared, didn't you?

135
00:07:09,040 --> 00:07:10,000
It's okay, it's okay.

136
00:07:10,839 --> 00:07:13,279
Thank God you came, Sheng Yuanzhou.

137
00:07:14,160 --> 00:07:14,800
All right.

138
00:07:20,160 --> 00:07:20,920
You're hurt.

139
00:07:22,120 --> 00:07:22,720
I'm fine.

140
00:07:23,639 --> 00:07:24,439
As long as you're okay.

141
00:07:25,399 --> 00:07:26,160
I'm fine.

142
00:07:26,399 --> 00:07:28,079
We've got more important things to do.

143
00:07:37,639 --> 00:07:39,199
What's going on? Where is she?

144
00:07:39,720 --> 00:07:40,480
We didn't catch her.

145
00:07:40,759 --> 00:07:41,600
We didn't catch her.

146
00:07:42,480 --> 00:07:44,439
Useless! You couldn't even catch one woman!

147
00:07:44,759 --> 00:07:45,560
We did catch her.

148
00:07:46,079 --> 00:07:48,959
But a pretty boy showed up and saved her.

149
00:07:50,279 --> 00:07:51,160
A pretty boy?

150
00:07:51,639 --> 00:07:53,040
That pretty boy is tough.

151
00:07:53,639 --> 00:07:54,920
Look what he did to me.

152
00:07:56,720 --> 00:07:57,959
And we didn't nab Lin Siqi either.

153
00:07:57,959 --> 00:07:58,879
What do we do now?

154
00:07:59,519 --> 00:08:00,680
Figure something out.

155
00:08:00,680 --> 00:08:01,480
What do we do?

156
00:08:01,480 --> 00:08:02,279
What can I do?

157
00:08:03,079 --> 00:08:03,759
You tell me.

158
00:08:04,040 --> 00:08:05,480
Why didn't you confirm it before the will reading?

159
00:08:05,480 --> 00:08:06,800
Why are you yelling at me?

160
00:08:07,040 --> 00:08:07,600
I was just anxious.

161
00:08:07,600 --> 00:08:08,920
I wanted to be with you already.

162
00:08:11,000 --> 00:08:13,000
It's all Lin Chengren's fault, that sly old fox.

163
00:08:13,279 --> 00:08:14,040
I stayed with him for years,

164
00:08:14,040 --> 00:08:14,720
and he left me so little.

165
00:08:14,720 --> 00:08:15,519
Enough.

166
00:08:17,600 --> 00:08:18,720
There's only one way now.

167
00:08:20,160 --> 00:08:22,199
At least your two sons still have inheritance rights.

168
00:08:24,240 --> 00:08:25,160
We need to hurry up

169
00:08:26,399 --> 00:08:27,560
and arrange for Lin Chengren's cremation.

170
00:08:27,879 --> 00:08:29,480
Then there'll be no proof

171
00:08:29,759 --> 00:08:31,000
the two boys aren't from the Lin family.

172
00:08:33,080 --> 00:08:33,639
Fine.

173
00:08:34,919 --> 00:08:36,480
As for Lin Siqi...

174
00:08:37,840 --> 00:08:39,159
She's a girl, after all.

175
00:08:39,679 --> 00:08:41,080
We'll deal with her later.

176
00:08:42,240 --> 00:08:43,240
How do we handle this?

177
00:08:43,960 --> 00:08:44,799
Kidnap her,

178
00:08:45,320 --> 00:08:46,159
or kill her?

179
00:08:52,039 --> 00:08:52,559
That's him.

180
00:08:53,080 --> 00:08:54,159
He's that pretty boy.

181
00:08:54,840 --> 00:08:56,879
I knew it, in broad daylight...

182
00:08:57,399 --> 00:08:59,159
in the hospital's underground garage...

183
00:08:59,960 --> 00:09:02,279
how could thugs just kidnap and assault someone?

184
00:09:03,279 --> 00:09:05,120
So it really was you two.

185
00:09:05,120 --> 00:09:06,440
Trying to kidnap Siqi.

186
00:09:06,720 --> 00:09:08,240
Stop slandering us!

187
00:09:08,639 --> 00:09:09,440
You got any proof?

188
00:09:10,120 --> 00:09:11,360
And we didn't nab Lin Siqi either.

189
00:09:11,360 --> 00:09:12,200
What do we do now?

190
00:09:13,080 --> 00:09:14,200
Figure something out.

191
00:09:14,200 --> 00:09:14,879
What do we do?

192
00:09:14,879 --> 00:09:15,600
What can I do?

193
00:09:16,080 --> 00:09:16,600
You tell me.

194
00:09:17,120 --> 00:09:18,399
Why didn't you confirm it before the will reading?

195
00:09:21,679 --> 00:09:22,559
Go take it back!

196
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:23,919
Do you think they'd dare?

197
00:09:24,279 --> 00:09:25,600
They wouldn't.

198
00:09:26,120 --> 00:09:26,960
Those two punks just now

199
00:09:26,960 --> 00:09:28,879
I already beat them into submission.

200
00:09:29,159 --> 00:09:29,840
It was them.

201
00:09:30,639 --> 00:09:31,919
They brought us here to find you two.

202
00:09:32,320 --> 00:09:34,039
Boss, we did what you asked.

203
00:09:34,639 --> 00:09:36,519
Can you let us go now?

204
00:09:36,840 --> 00:09:38,120
Don't do this again.

205
00:09:38,679 --> 00:09:39,039
Get lost.

206
00:09:39,480 --> 00:09:41,120
Okay, we won't, we won't!

207
00:09:41,240 --> 00:09:41,519
Go, go, go!

208
00:10:01,600 --> 00:10:04,039
Siqi, I was bewitched for a moment.

209
00:10:04,039 --> 00:10:05,759
I only hired them to scare you.

210
00:10:06,200 --> 00:10:06,919
Are you hurt?

211
00:10:06,919 --> 00:10:08,360
Did they hit you too hard?

212
00:10:10,480 --> 00:10:11,480
Sign this agreement.

213
00:10:17,720 --> 00:10:18,639
What is this?

214
00:10:18,879 --> 00:10:20,440
You want me to give up my assets and custody?

215
00:10:20,440 --> 00:10:21,440
Are you insane?

216
00:10:21,799 --> 00:10:22,639
I'm not pressing charges

217
00:10:23,080 --> 00:10:24,559
because I don't want my two younger brothers

218
00:10:24,559 --> 00:10:25,720
to have a criminal mother.

219
00:10:26,080 --> 00:10:27,000
If you don't want to go to prison,

220
00:10:27,960 --> 00:10:29,159
sign this agreement.

221
00:10:29,480 --> 00:10:31,039
You're trying to show no mercy!

222
00:10:31,279 --> 00:10:33,200
Compared to what you've done,

223
00:10:33,879 --> 00:10:35,159
I've been merciful enough.

224
00:10:37,360 --> 00:10:38,879
You're not leaving me a cent.

225
00:10:39,200 --> 00:10:40,559
How am I supposed to live?

226
00:10:40,879 --> 00:10:41,679
Either go to prison,

227
00:10:41,919 --> 00:10:42,720
or sign the agreement.

228
00:10:43,679 --> 00:10:44,320
Choose.

229
00:10:44,799 --> 00:10:45,720
My testimony,

230
00:10:45,960 --> 00:10:47,120
and the evidence I've got...

231
00:10:47,320 --> 00:10:48,159
Take a guess.

232
00:10:48,600 --> 00:10:49,919
How many years will you do?

233
00:10:53,799 --> 00:10:55,879
Siqi, we're family.

234
00:10:56,240 --> 00:10:58,159
You... for your two younger brothers' sake...

235
00:10:58,360 --> 00:10:59,879
let me off this once.

236
00:11:00,440 --> 00:11:00,960
Siqi!

237
00:11:01,320 --> 00:11:03,919
Qiqi, at least leave me somewhere to live!

238
00:11:04,120 --> 00:11:04,600
Qiqi!

239
00:11:05,720 --> 00:11:06,200
Fine.

240
00:11:08,840 --> 00:11:09,919
Then go to prison.

241
00:11:18,159 --> 00:11:18,960
I'll sign.

242
00:11:19,480 --> 00:11:20,240
I'll sign.

243
00:11:39,559 --> 00:11:41,639
Should we go to the hospital anyway?

244
00:11:42,159 --> 00:11:42,679
No need.

245
00:11:43,440 --> 00:11:44,639
Just put some medicine on it for me.

246
00:11:45,399 --> 00:11:47,679
Then bear with it.

247
00:11:50,279 --> 00:11:51,600
I'm not a kid.

248
00:11:52,240 --> 00:11:53,120
It'll pass if I tough it out.

249
00:11:53,759 --> 00:11:55,120
Even adults feel pain.

250
00:12:09,600 --> 00:12:11,960
So you're really planning to do it alone,

251
00:12:11,960 --> 00:12:13,080
living with your younger brothers?

252
00:12:15,759 --> 00:12:16,600
Even though

253
00:12:16,960 --> 00:12:18,519
they aren't my dad's biological kids,

254
00:12:18,960 --> 00:12:21,159
we grew up together.

255
00:12:21,840 --> 00:12:22,759
We called each other sister and brothers.

256
00:12:23,440 --> 00:12:25,559
We've been a family for a long time.

257
00:12:26,120 --> 00:12:27,480
Blood is thicker than water,

258
00:12:27,799 --> 00:12:28,720
but I think

259
00:12:28,960 --> 00:12:30,360
the ones who truly live together

260
00:12:30,799 --> 00:12:31,960
are the real family.

261
00:12:37,120 --> 00:12:37,720
Yeah.

262
00:12:39,279 --> 00:12:40,759
Only the ones who truly live together

263
00:12:41,600 --> 00:12:42,440
can be called family.

264
00:12:54,759 --> 00:12:55,360
Today...

265
00:12:57,559 --> 00:12:58,240
Thank you.

266
00:12:58,600 --> 00:12:59,440
For what?

267
00:13:00,320 --> 00:13:01,120
If anything,

268
00:13:01,480 --> 00:13:03,000
I should thank you for bandaging me up.

269
00:13:09,039 --> 00:13:09,440
Um...

270
00:13:09,919 --> 00:13:11,000
Take care of your wound.

271
00:13:11,159 --> 00:13:12,320
Don't get it wet these next few days.

272
00:13:13,519 --> 00:13:13,840
Okay.

273
00:13:18,240 --> 00:13:18,639
Well...

274
00:13:19,480 --> 00:13:21,159
Be safe on your way back.

275
00:13:21,799 --> 00:13:22,960
I'm heading home.

276
00:13:29,840 --> 00:13:30,480
Siqi, I...

277
00:13:37,919 --> 00:13:38,320
Good night.

278
00:13:44,360 --> 00:13:44,759
Good night.

279
00:13:45,679 --> 00:13:46,240
Go on, get back.

280
00:13:46,399 --> 00:13:47,039
Get some rest.

281
00:14:04,320 --> 00:14:06,080
You two are still young.

282
00:14:06,320 --> 00:14:07,519
Breaking up and getting back together is normal.

283
00:14:08,080 --> 00:14:09,360
Siqi is a good kid.

284
00:14:09,639 --> 00:14:10,600
Staying friends isn't a bad idea either.

285
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:15,200
Why are you just like your dad,

286
00:14:15,200 --> 00:14:17,120
always interested in this beat-up junk?

287
00:14:17,879 --> 00:14:18,320
Boss,

288
00:14:19,200 --> 00:14:19,799
how much is this?

289
00:14:20,039 --> 00:14:21,240
One price, 50 yuan.

290
00:14:21,799 --> 00:14:22,200
Fifty?

291
00:14:22,200 --> 00:14:22,799
I'll take it.

292
00:14:23,600 --> 00:14:24,480
Don't waste your money.

293
00:14:25,320 --> 00:14:27,200
Mom, this is really good stuff.

294
00:14:28,360 --> 00:14:29,720
One look and you can tell it's fake.

295
00:14:30,360 --> 00:14:31,480
The clay body of blue and white porcelain,

296
00:14:31,480 --> 00:14:32,480
the glaze color and craftsmanship,

297
00:14:32,879 --> 00:14:34,120
and its sheen and sound...

298
00:14:34,360 --> 00:14:36,159
Old celadon is very delicate.

299
00:14:36,600 --> 00:14:37,240
And the glaze surface is...

300
00:14:37,240 --> 00:14:38,639
Quit rambling on here.

301
00:14:40,360 --> 00:14:40,879
Go home and cook.

302
00:14:41,200 --> 00:14:42,080
Wouldn't that be nice.

303
00:14:44,200 --> 00:14:44,480
Let's go.

304
00:14:46,559 --> 00:14:47,559
Boss, I'll take it.

305
00:14:47,879 --> 00:14:48,720
Consider it buying a lottery ticket.

306
00:14:51,679 --> 00:14:53,759
A viral influencer was filming a vlog,

307
00:14:54,039 --> 00:14:55,200
and casually, at a small stall,

308
00:14:55,360 --> 00:14:56,480
bought a celadon cup.

309
00:14:56,679 --> 00:14:57,759
An antique expert saw it,

310
00:14:57,960 --> 00:14:59,919
and it turned out to be from the Ming Dynasty.

311
00:15:00,679 --> 00:15:01,200
Mom!

312
00:15:02,480 --> 00:15:02,879
Mom!

313
00:15:04,159 --> 00:15:04,720
What is it?

314
00:15:05,320 --> 00:15:06,360
I'm busy right now.

315
00:15:06,840 --> 00:15:07,840
Mom, look.

316
00:15:10,679 --> 00:15:11,759
That's amazing.

317
00:15:12,360 --> 00:15:14,120
Since when could you appraise antiques?

318
00:15:14,679 --> 00:15:15,639
I don't know either.

319
00:15:15,960 --> 00:15:16,759
I just can.

320
00:15:17,960 --> 00:15:19,480
My son really is a genius.

321
00:15:19,919 --> 00:15:20,559
Takes after me.

322
00:15:21,840 --> 00:15:23,240
But what a shame.

323
00:15:23,679 --> 00:15:24,360
We didn't buy it then.

324
00:15:25,320 --> 00:15:26,000
What's the big deal?

325
00:15:26,200 --> 00:15:27,679
Everyone has their own luck with money.

326
00:15:28,080 --> 00:15:30,080
If it's not meant for us, it won't be ours.

327
00:15:30,799 --> 00:15:31,360
Besides,

328
00:15:31,720 --> 00:15:33,200
my son's so smart,

329
00:15:33,600 --> 00:15:35,480
how could he not find treasures later?

330
00:15:36,799 --> 00:15:37,120
Time to eat.

331
00:15:37,600 --> 00:15:38,240
Go tell your dad to eat.

332
00:15:38,240 --> 00:15:38,519
Okay.

333
00:15:40,279 --> 00:15:41,960
Looks like Lin Chengren's death

334
00:15:42,639 --> 00:15:44,440
has a lot to do with Sheng Shizhong.

335
00:15:45,879 --> 00:15:47,000
He wanted to silence him.

336
00:15:47,000 --> 00:15:47,840
It must be because

337
00:15:47,840 --> 00:15:49,639
Lin Chengren used Bai Zimei's situation

338
00:15:50,159 --> 00:15:51,039
to threaten him.

339
00:15:52,240 --> 00:15:53,759
Bai Zimei could clearly talk about

340
00:15:53,759 --> 00:15:55,399
the Key of Fate and switching identities.

341
00:15:56,799 --> 00:15:57,559
That proves

342
00:15:58,159 --> 00:15:59,720
she must've used the Key of Fate

343
00:15:59,840 --> 00:16:00,720
to learn the truth.

344
00:16:01,720 --> 00:16:02,759
Which means,

345
00:16:03,240 --> 00:16:04,360
the current Sheng Shizhong

346
00:16:05,200 --> 00:16:07,039
is the driver from back then, Hu Jin,

347
00:16:08,519 --> 00:16:10,039
using the Key of Fate

348
00:16:10,360 --> 00:16:12,279
to swap identities with the real Sheng Shizhong.

349
00:16:14,000 --> 00:16:15,840
If he has the Key of Fate,

350
00:16:16,200 --> 00:16:17,519
where would he hide it?

351
00:16:22,840 --> 00:16:24,960
You can't keep coming here all the time.

352
00:16:25,159 --> 00:16:26,559
Your father will lose his temper.

353
00:16:28,480 --> 00:16:29,120
Granny Shen,

354
00:16:29,360 --> 00:16:31,720
I remember my dad wasn't like this before.

355
00:16:31,919 --> 00:16:32,759
He used to dote on me.

356
00:16:33,279 --> 00:16:34,559
Why is he so fierce now?

357
00:16:35,320 --> 00:16:37,080
Isn't it because your younger brother died?

358
00:16:39,200 --> 00:16:39,799
My younger brother?

359
00:16:40,919 --> 00:16:42,279
That poor child.

360
00:16:42,480 --> 00:16:44,679
He died before he was even born.

361
00:16:45,360 --> 00:16:46,840
When your mom first got pregnant,

362
00:16:47,080 --> 00:16:48,720
your dad was over the moon.

363
00:16:49,720 --> 00:16:50,960
Before the baby was even born,

364
00:16:51,120 --> 00:16:52,399
the name was already picked out.

365
00:16:53,519 --> 00:16:55,240
Sheng Yuanhe.

366
00:16:59,120 --> 00:17:00,080
You're saying,

367
00:17:00,639 --> 00:17:01,600
because my mom miscarried,

368
00:17:02,240 --> 00:17:04,240
my dad's personality completely changed?

369
00:17:05,839 --> 00:17:07,799
Back then, your mom had an episode,

370
00:17:08,200 --> 00:17:09,599
and secretly took medicine.

371
00:17:10,960 --> 00:17:12,440
Only later did we realize

372
00:17:13,880 --> 00:17:14,839
the baby was gone.

373
00:17:15,160 --> 00:17:16,720
Your dad was devastated.

374
00:17:17,079 --> 00:17:18,720
It hit him really hard.

375
00:17:19,680 --> 00:17:20,279
After that,

376
00:17:20,759 --> 00:17:22,759
he was like a different person.

377
00:17:23,160 --> 00:17:25,160
If Bai Zimei hadn't lost her mind,

378
00:17:25,759 --> 00:17:26,799
then she would've known

379
00:17:26,799 --> 00:17:28,359
that baby wasn't her husband's.

380
00:17:28,640 --> 00:17:29,559
It was Hu Jin's.

381
00:17:30,039 --> 00:17:31,480
That's why she aborted the baby.

382
00:17:32,519 --> 00:17:34,400
If what Sheng Shizhong cared about most

383
00:17:34,720 --> 00:17:36,640
was that unborn child...

384
00:17:37,519 --> 00:17:38,480
How pitiful.

385
00:17:38,839 --> 00:17:40,359
Such a good family.

386
00:17:42,039 --> 00:17:44,880
Granny Shen, where is my younger brother's grave?

387
00:17:45,799 --> 00:17:46,599
I don't know.

388
00:17:46,759 --> 00:17:49,160
The child died as soon as he was born,

389
00:17:49,400 --> 00:17:50,960
your dad took him away in his arms.

390
00:17:51,359 --> 00:17:52,640
I don't know where he was buried.
